| A-041 | 005F2 blocks additional `return-with-deficiencies` attempts once an application is already `application_status = incomplete_returned`. | The opened source docs define the first deficiency return to incomplete state and borrower resubmission, but do not define repeat staff returns before resubmission. Blocking repeats avoids duplicate open deficiency rows and duplicate borrower communications without inventing a repeat-return business rule. | `docs/source/data-model.md` `loan_application_status`; `docs/source/functional-spec.md` M03 deficiency flow; `docs/source/screen-spec.md` S12; `docs/slices/005F2-deficiency-return-status-contract-hardening.md` | 005F2-deficiency-return-status-contract-hardening and future portal deficiency response/resubmission slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-09 | Future borrower resubmission work should define the source-backed transition from `incomplete_returned` back to submitted/completeness review before any later repeat-return behavior is allowed. |
| A-042 | 005FA generates portal activation/password-reset OTP challenges server-side, stores only OTP hashes, and records a pending communication-shell row without calling a real SMS/email provider. Tests use an explicit `PORTAL_AUTH_TEST_OTP` setting to simulate receipt. PAN/Aadhaar last-four verification currently compares against the stored encrypted-value placeholder strings because no decrypt/search adapter exists yet. | MP01/MP02 require OTP, but source docs do not specify a delivery provider and this sandbox has no network. Security docs forbid storing raw OTPs and sensitive values. The existing 003I communication shell is the source-compliant boundary until a provider adapter exists. | `docs/source/screen-spec-member-portal.md` MP01/MP02; `docs/source/security-privacy.md` §10 and sensitive-data list; `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §5; `docs/slices/005FA-member-portal-authentication.md` | 005FA-member-portal-authentication and future notification/provider/security-hardening slices | High | Yes | 2026-07-09 | Replace placeholder last-four checks with a proper decrypt/hash-verification adapter when sensitive-value services exist; wire OTP delivery to the real notification provider when selected. |
| A-043 | 005FB exposes `/api/v1/portal/produce-supply/` as an empty read-only shell with `source_status = model_not_implemented` until a `produce_supply_records` model/table is implemented. | `data-model.md` §11.6 defines the table, but the current Django members app has no corresponding model or migration. Inventing supply rows or deriving them from crop plans would create unsourced business data. | `docs/source/data-model.md` §11.6; `docs/source/screen-spec-member-portal.md` MP03/MP04 and permissions matrix; `docs/slices/005FB-member-portal-dashboard-profile-and-supply-view.md` | 005FB-member-portal-dashboard-profile-and-supply-view and future active-member/produce-supply slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-09 | Add the model-backed list and summary once the source-backed produce-supply persistence slice exists; until then the portal must show an empty state, not mock history. |
| A-044 | 005G2 returns `401 INVALID_TOKEN` for old-token portal dashboard/profile/supply/application/password-change calls after the linked `PortalAccount` becomes suspended or inactive, rather than a portal-route-level `403`, because those routes use the shared session-bound bearer validator before portal scope is resolved. The validator revokes the session with reason `portal_account_status_changed`. | The slice allowed choosing exact route-level status by existing auth helper semantics, and the existing route stack authenticates the bearer session before route-specific permission checks. A single invalid-session boundary avoids exposing stale portal claims or own-data permissions. | `docs/slices/005G2-member-portal-session-and-audit-contract-hardening.md`; `docs/working/digests/epic-005-application-intake.md`; `docs/working/API_CONTRACTS.md` | 005G2-member-portal-session-and-audit-contract-hardening and future portal/staff route slices | Medium | No | 2026-07-10 | Implemented and tested for `/auth/me`, password change, portal own-data, and portal application routes. Staff/non-portal valid sessions still receive `403 PERMISSION_DENIED` on portal routes. |
| A-045 | 005H rejection-note creation keeps `LoanApplication.application_status` unchanged as `submitted` and stores only `RejectionNote.note_status = draft/sent`; it does not invent a generic intake rejection status. | `screen-spec.md` S14 says the application status is updated after rejection-note output, but the implemented/source-backed application status vocabulary currently has `draft`, `submitted`, `incomplete_returned`, and `reference_generated` for this intake stage, while data-model rejection statuses are tied to later credit-assessment/sanction concepts. | `docs/source/screen-spec.md` S14; `docs/source/data-model.md` §13.6 and loan-application status vocabulary; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §21.3-§21.4; `docs/slices/005H-rejection-note-shell.md` | 005H-rejection-note-shell and future eligibility/appraisal/sanction rejection slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-10 | Future appraisal/rejection slices should define the source-backed stored rejected status and then decide whether rejection-note creation, approval, or send performs that transition. |
| A-046 | 006A returns `member_active_check = manual_evidence_required` when a member is active but no source-backed continuous produce/service history exists; it does not infer BR-004 through BR-007 from membership status alone. Existing verified `Member.active_member_status` facts can still produce `pass` or `relaxation`. | BR-004 through BR-007 require produce/service history or relaxation evidence, but current persistence has only member/profile summary fields and no source-backed history rows for continuous-year calculation. Inventing a supply-history calculation would create a business rule the source documents do not state. | `docs/source/functional-spec.md` BR-004 through BR-007; `docs/source/data-model.md` §14.1; `docs/working/digests/epic-006-eligibility-loan-limit-appraisal.md` | 006A-active-member-eligibility-service and future active-member/supply-history slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-10 | Add source-backed produce/service history models and replace this manual-evidence result when the active-member history slice is implemented. |
| A-047 | 006C treats exactly one active, effective, Board-referenced `LoanPolicyConfig` as the explicit operative loan-limit configuration. A configured percentage produces `valuation_per_share × percentage`; a configured per-share cap is the per-share ceiling; when both are present the lower per-share value applies. No applicable policy, multiple applicable policies, or neither positive share rule blocks calculation without success evidence. | The source requires percentage or per-share-cap configuration and says the API must expose the exact rule/version/source, but it does not spell out the interaction when both fields are populated. Treating the cap as a ceiling is the standard meaning of cap, reproduces the source §23.1 example (`10% of ₹2,000 = ₹200` with a ₹200 cap), and avoids choosing 30%, 10%, or ₹200 in code. | `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §23.1-§23.3; `docs/source/data-model.md` §14.2/§35.1; `docs/source/functional-spec.md` BR-019 through BR-025 and M01-FR-005/M01-FR-006 | 006C-loan-limit-configuration-and-calculator and future policy-governance slices | High | Yes | 2026-07-10 | The values remain versioned configuration, never hard-coded. If the client confirms mutually exclusive percentage/cap modes or another interaction, add an explicit rule-mode field and migrate calculation tests without rewriting historical assessment snapshots. |
| A-048 | 006D's policy-source snapshot columns allow null/blank only for database compatibility with assessment rows created before the migration. Every successful post-006D calculate/rerun stores policy config UUID, name, and Board reference; a legacy row is never enriched by reading mutable policy configuration during GET. | Existing 006C rows did not retain enough data to reconstruct policy source immutably. Backfilling from current policy rows could attach changed or ambiguous metadata and would violate historical integrity. | `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §23.3; `docs/source/data-model.md` §14.2, §35.1, §36.1; `docs/source/test-plan.md` MOD-LIMIT-009/MOD-LIMIT-010 | 006D-loan-limit-snapshot-storage | Medium | No | 2026-07-10 | If a deployed environment contains pre-006D assessments, an authorized successful rerun is the safe path to populate the new snapshot fields. GET returns null policy-source values for untouched legacy rows rather than consulting mutable config. |
| A-049 | Until the source defines how selected `LandHolding.area_acres`, `CropPlan.planned_area_acres`, and nullable profile `land_area_under_cultivation_acres` are reconciled for BR-020, 006C2 will block calculation when the applicable verified acreage facts disagree; it will not invent a min/max/priority formula. | Functional BR-020 requires acreage under cultivation, while the API/data model expose three related acreage facts without a precedence or reconciliation rule. Current 006C sums selected owned acreage and can overstate the land limit when cultivation evidence is lower. | `docs/source/functional-spec.md` BR-020/BR-022; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §23.1-§23.3; `docs/source/data-model.md` §10.2, §11.7-§11.8, §14.2, §35.1; architecture review `2026-07-10_092630_architecture_review` | 006C2-cultivated-acreage-source-hardening and future policy confirmation | High | Yes | 2026-07-10 | Safe interim behavior is a structured validation blocker with no assessment/audit/workflow mutation. If the client confirms an authoritative source or formula, replace the equality guard, version the rule, and preserve existing snapshots. |
| A-050 | Application Detail composes API checklist rows with the existing card, badge, grid, tab, and empty-state patterns instead of reusing `DocumentChecklist`, because that prototype component imports `mockData` and synthesizes borrower/nominee/witness identifiers, documentation execution, security, and readiness facts. | 005I4 requires the real application detail to display API checklist rows directly and forbids synthetic lifecycle/readiness facts; reusing the existing mock-backed component would violate the slice and expose invented values. | `docs/slices/005I4-application-detail-backend-state-hardening.md`; `docs/working/FRONTEND_DESIGN_RULES.md`; `sfpcl-lms/src/components/loan/DocumentChecklist.tsx` | 005I4-application-detail-backend-state-hardening and future documentation UI wiring | Medium | No | 2026-07-10 | The composition reuses only approved prototype classes/components and introduces no new colours, typography, card, badge, table, or layout system. Replace it with the owning future API-backed documentation component when that workflow lands. |

